SCHEDULER CONTROLLER FLOW

-- @RestController--class mark itself as request handler and create restful 
webservcie.
-- @RefreshScope-- load config prop from config server(bind the config
 package to load when the request hits).
-- @RequestMapping--used to map the request to the specified class and
 method and make web addressable.
-- @Tag--(filtered)mostly used in test class and execute the tets plan.  
development team specify the values 'fast','slow'.etc
-- @SecurityRequirements-- define the spectific set of security to the endpoints
-- @Autowired-- connect the other class function automatically.dependency 
injection
-- @Qualifier--define the preference,when the multiple bean has same type 
present in it.
-- @value--inject the value which managed by spring bean
-- @ApiOperation--is an unique combination of api call and hhtp method,
describe the results of successful rest api.specify general
 return type.
-- @RefreshScope--used to load the config prop values in config server,the
 server should run before the config client appln.
-- @Scheduled --used to trigger the scheduled task for specific  time period.
-- @Transactional--metadata that specifies the information of the transaction on 
a method.
-- @SuppressWarnings--instruct the complier to ignore specified complier
 warnings un annotated elements and all pgm elmnts inside the elemnts

